dcterms:description: DeepPCB is a real dataset of 1500 samples obtained by a linear scan CCD, which contains six common PCB defects: open, short, mouse bite, spur, copper, and pin-hole. The dataset is used to train models with high-quality datasets and test them under various noise conditions.
dcterms:title: DeepPCB
